{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.22",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 22 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:2",
      "text": "“Can a man be profitable to God? Surely he who is wise is profitable to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:3",
      "text": "Is it any pleasure to the Almighty if you are righteous, or is it gain to him if you make your ways blameless?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:4",
      "text": "Is it for your fear of him that he reproves you, and enters into judgment with you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:5",
      "text": "Is not your wickedness great? There is no end to your iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:6",
      "text": "For you have exacted pledges of your brothers for nothing, and stripped the naked of their clothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:7",
      "text": "You have given no water to the weary to drink, and you have withheld bread from the hungry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:8",
      "text": "The man with power possessed the land, and the favored man dwelt in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:9",
      "text": "You have sent widows away empty, and the arms of the fatherless were crushed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:10",
      "text": "Therefore snares are round about you, and sudden terror overwhelms you;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:11",
      "text": "your light is darkened, so that you cannot see, and a flood of water covers you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:12",
      "text": "“Is not God high in the heavens? See the highest stars, how lofty they are!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:13",
      "text": "Therefore you say, ‘What does God know? Can he judge through the deep darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:14",
      "text": "Thick clouds enwrap him, so that he does not see, and he walks on the vault of heaven.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:15",
      "text": "Will you keep to the old way which wicked men have trod?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:16",
      "text": "They were snatched away before their time; their foundation was washed away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:17",
      "text": "They said to God, ‘Depart from us,’ and ‘What can the Almighty do to us?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:18",
      "text": "Yet he filled their houses with good things— but the counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:19",
      "text": "The righteous see it and are glad; the innocent laugh them to scorn,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:20",
      "text": "saying, ‘Surely our adversaries are cut off, and what they left the fire has consumed.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:21",
      "text": "“Agree with God, and be at peace; thereby good will come to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:22",
      "text": "Receive instruction from his mouth, and lay up his words in your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:23",
      "text": "If you return to the Almighty and humble yourself, if you remove unrighteousness far from your tents,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:24",
      "text": "if you lay gold in the dust, and gold of Ophir among the stones of the torrent bed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:25",
      "text": "and if the Almighty is your gold, and your precious silver;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:26",
      "text": "then you will delight yourself in the Almighty, and lift up your face to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:27",
      "text": "You will make your prayer to him, and he will hear you; and you will pay your vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:28",
      "text": "You will decide on a matter, and it will be established for you, and light will shine on your ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:29",
      "text": "For God abases the proud, but he saves the lowly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.22.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:30",
      "text": "He delivers the innocent man; you will be delivered through the cleanness of your hands.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
